                           HARK! A MESSAGE FROM YOUR SQUIRE

     .~"~.~"~.
    /  o   o  \      Greetings, m'lord! 'Tis I, your faithful
   |  >  ◡  <  |     (if somewhat clumsy) digital squire!
    \  ___  /        
     |~|♦|~|         Today's Ancient Wisdom:
    d|     |b        "Do not force yourself to write when 
                      you have nothing to say."
                            - An ancient scribe from the East

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  📜 Quick Commands for Your Literary Quest:
  
  • scribe          - Begin a new manuscript
  • scroll          - Browse your written works  
  • chronicle       - View thy writing statistics
  • summon [name]   - Open an existing scroll
  • seal            - Save and export your work

  💡 Squire's Tip of the Day:
  "Remember to save thy work frequently, lest the candle 
   blow out and all be lost to darkness!"

